d in water and boil it or simmer it and he would add to that licorice. You could buy licorice in these rolls, like - you know, like a long piece - like a stick of licorice, and it tasted horrid licorice did and he'd break pieces off and put this licorice 
into the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15086356\charrsid7763791 linseed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6423686\charrsid7763791 
. And it used to stand in a jug on the grate and when he was troubled he'd have a - he'd get a cup and have a drink of this licorice which was horrid. Yes. Yes, but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
