tables or tinned fruit much in those days. Not - not in tin - I know I used to fetch potatoes I always remember fetching potatoes for me mother, and I always remember how much I paid for these potatoes. They were always five pound for fourpence. That was 
t
he price of potatoes for years and years and years and years. I used to fetch these potatoes. And I remember - I remember once my mother sending me to fetch some - peas, used to by these peas loose and - these peas were in a paper bag so - I was coming ho
me with these peas, carrying them by the top, when the bag burst and the peas went all over the pavement. Surprising how you remember these things. Yes.
