es, the grocer, Hallen and Williams was a - was a real high class grocers, yes, in Longton, and I used to go and fetch the groceries, quite a parcel, struggle home with the parcel. Malling and Williams in Market Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2775584 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6423686\charrsid7763791 You told me a tale about when you went to get some butter one time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7343200 OB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6423686\charrsid7763791 
Yes. Yes. Yes, I would, yes. Yes. Well each year at Shrove time there came a fair into the town, and it was a very big fair indeed and - Collins, the - fair people, they used to come along with all the - hobby hor
ses and roundabouts and swings and - and all - lots of other similar people came as well, but the main people were Collins, it was called Collins' fair. And - on the hoardings in the town there was posted big posters which said, come and see the man eatin
g
 lion. So - I wanted me mother to let me go to the fairground and she - couldn't let me go because she thought I was too young. However she wanted to - she wanted a pound of butter so I persuaded her to let me go down the town which was close to the fair 
t
o fetch this pound of butter from the Maypole Shop. Yes. So I thought well now, here's a chance for me to go to the fairground. So I got - I got the butter, and I think I paid one and fourpence for the pound of butter at the Maypole shop and then I went a
l
ong to the fairground and - I went to the - this - wild beast show to go and see this man eating lion. So - when you - you - you went up a few steps onto a platform where the men were - you know - shouting away, telling you all about it, and down some ste
ps onto the ground floor in the - in the show. However being small I - I went back and I stood on the steps as you start to go down into the - into the show so as I could get a good view and - when the lion tamer came in - inside they'd got a - a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15086356\charrsid7763791 brazier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6423686\charrsid7763791 , a
 fire burning, and this - and the - the - a man got an iron bar and got this iron bar red hot and then put it through the bars of the cage and it make the lion jump round like mad, I suppose that was all part of the business. And then the lion tamer stood
 
outside the door - inside - there was a little cage as he went in just outside the main cage and - each time he'd open the door to go in the cage the lion sprang round at the - to the - to come out - to the door. However, he was a bit too late to close th
e
 door and the lion come round the door, passed his legs and through this little cage that he was standing in and jumped down amongst the people. Well - there was a real rush, everybody was in a panic and the lion came through the people towards where I wa
s
 standing to go out. And the lion came straight up to me and I put me foot on its forehead and - that stopped the lion - probably the lion would have gone up the steps and out into the street, but instead of that it - the lion turned and went underneath t
he platform. And I got knocked down and I was on the floor and people were walking }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15086356\charrsid7763791 over me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
