I - no, I - no, I've no idea. My elder brother - was rather a disappointment to his parents. And he was the only one that had a higher education. But - he was sort of broke way from the family somehow
 or other and - my father was rather friendly with the - with a - the bank manager and - a manufacturer or two and - also the lawyer, so - my father didn't know what to do with my elder brother, he was the barum scarum of the family and he was like that r
i
ght through his life. So they told my father, oh send him to sea. You see, make a sailor of him. So - he was seventeen and - my father sent him to be an apprentice midshipman on sailing sip, that was in the days when they were sailing ships. And - they ri
gged him out with everything he wanted and - with this big chest full of clothes and he went and joined this sailing ship - in Hamburg and it sailed to Australia and it took the four months to get to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15086356\charrsid7763791 Australia}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6423686\charrsid7763791  by sailing by the - by the wind you know on a s
ailing ship. Well it was a terrible time so I believe and when my brother got to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15086356\charrsid7763791 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
