hing, 'til one day someone who used to live in Longton met him and they wrote home to tell his parents about him. You know, he was roaming. So of course you know how mothers are, they get distressed about their - their children - she got quite distressed 
a
bout it, and me father - paid or wired money for him to come home. And when he came home - he'd hardly got a bit of clothing on and I remember me mother taking him - going the town and buying him a new suit and fixing him up. But - when he - he - when he 
came home again we couldn't do much good with him. He wasn't - he wasn't a bad - he wasn't a bad - yes, he was -
