e - after the first war - oh after the second war - yes, yes, but he spent his life in the Army. However, when he came back he went to work - at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Stoke{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Town Hall{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} - and - he studied accountancy in - in his spare time and became an accountant. And he opened o
ut on his own in Stoke as an accountant. And he did very well. And his son's still carrying it on, that's his son, Houseman. Yes, well - yes, well it was his father, was the first real - friend - boy friend that I had.
