{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} has lent me a book and you'll see it and it's - it - it's got in this book advertising the star cars.
 And - I don't whether I ever told you about - what you did for a spare wheel, and it shows you in this book as {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose} - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} lent me - shows you the spare wheel which they used in those days. Well - it - it was a rim only with a tyre on, no spoils at all 
in it, it was a rim and a tyre and tube. But on this rim were fastened four clamps, so that when your tyre was punctured on the car you were able to - you know, the tyre's soft and you were able to push these hooks inside the rim where the tyre goes under
, these four - it had had four round the wheel, and then you could screw them up like a thumbscrew and you screwed - that fastened this wheel, this spare ri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1074794\charrsid7763791 m}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6423686\charrsid7763791 , by the side of the punctured wheel. And that's what brought you home. Yes. And I'll show it to you in a picture, it's out of this book belongs to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Alice{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, she lent it me. And I was surprised to see these Star cars because - nobody ever remember Star cars.
\par 
